   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Units in a redundant system<ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph "> or a dual
system that work in parallel to supply one load</ph> must communicate
with each other. The behavior of a redundant system is complex and
will depend on multiple factors.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">As an option in redundant<ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph "> or dual</ph> systems, an output couple switch
can be used to temporarily separate<ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph "> or share</ph> the load between the units.</p>
         <p platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/p ">As an option
in redundant systems with individual batteries, a battery couple switch
can be used to temporarily connect both individual batteries to one
unit.</p>
